characteristics.name: Age
characteristics.description: Age calculated as the integer part of the difference between the date of informed consent and the date of birth, divided by 365.25.

characteristics.name: Body Mass Index
characteristics.description: Body mass index (BMI) will be calculated at baseline.

characteristics.name: Treatment Cohort
characteristics.description: Participant cohort classification: Cohort 1 (treatment experienced, >28 days WD therapy) or Cohort 2 (treatment naïve, ≤28 days WD therapy).

characteristics.name: Medical/Surgical History
characteristics.description: Participant's medical and surgical history at baseline.

characteristics.name: Prior medications used to treat Wilson Disease
characteristics.description: Prior medications used by the participant to treat Wilson Disease.

characteristics.name: Baseline copper balance
characteristics.description: Mean daily copper balance measured during the pretreatment period (Days -4 through -1).

characteristics.name: Baseline molybdenum balance
characteristics.description: Mean daily molybdenum balance measured during the pretreatment period.

characteristics.name: Baseline laboratory assessments
characteristics.description: Laboratory test results from samples collected at baseline.

characteristics.name: Baseline physical examination
characteristics.description: Findings from the physical examination conducted at baseline.
